Program Agreements
A. Adoption of community service-Oriented Policing System (CSOP) the CSOP framework balster coordination and cooperation the citenry, local executives and lntegrated Law enforcement and Public safety agencies existing in the locality undertaken through program or project implementation, including sharing of information, funds, personnel, and logistics;

B. Development POPS Plan/Integrated Area/Community Public safety Plan (IACPSP) in coordinate with the guidelines that will provided by DILG;

C. Implementation of joint programs, project, services and services within the CSOP framework as outlined in the POPS Plan; and D. Adoption and implementation of other programs, which can contribute to the enchantment of access to justify delivery of justice services.

The signing of MOA was attended by Municipal Mayor Floro S. Gandam Sr. along with Municipal Chief of  Police, PLt. Col, Romy Castañares, PNP Faith Based Leader, Pastor Joemar G Alang
